title: QB tiers for every FBS program: Returning stars, blue-chip freshmen, transfers and, of course, Arch Manning
description: From Clemson to Kennesaw State, David Hale ranks all 136 FBS school quarterbacks into tiers.
author: David Hale

title: Clark, Fever back investigation: No place for hate
description: Fever players on Monday supported the WNBA's investigation into allegations of "hateful fan comments" toward the Sky's Angel Reese.
author: Michael Voepel

title: Wait goes on as Salah bids to break Premier League records
description: Mohamed Salah's wait goes on in his bid to beat the Premier League's goal involvement and assist records - but he has one more chance this season.

title: 'Writing on the wall' - what does future hold for Grealish?
description: Manchester City midfielder Jack Grealish may have to leave the club this summer with "the writing on the wall" for him, says their former goalkeeper Shay Given.

title: Cunha set to join Man Utd
description: Matheus Cunha is set to join Manchester United after the season ends this weekend.

title: Merson's Arteta warning: 'Top two by Christmas or Arsenal will go for someone else'
description: Paul Merson thinks Mikel Arteta has until Christmas to prove he is the right manager for Arsenal after another trophyless season at the Emirates Stadium..

title: MLB to experiment in minors with technology challenges for checked swings
description: Major League Baseball will experiment with a technology system to challenge checked swing calls in the Class A Florida State League starting Tuesday. Using a Hawk-Eye system, a checked swing call can be challenged by either the team at bat or on defense. Short of 45 degrees will be called a no swing.

title: Golden State Warriors jersey history - No. 12 - Levi Fontaine (1970-71)
description: During his time suiting up for the Warriors, Fontaine wore only jersey No. 12 and put up 3.8 points per game.
